The Municipal Assessor furnish the Municipal Treasurer on or before the 31st day of December of each year, an assessment roll containing a list of  all real property, whether taxable or exempt, located within the territorial jurisdiction of the Municipal Government of Lezo, Aklan and  a list of all persons whose real properties have been newly assessed or reassessed and the values of such properties;
The Municipal Treasurer prepare a duly certified list showing the name of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant to serve as the basis in setting up the beginning balance of RPT/SET Receivable in the books of accounts. In such manner, the related receivable account and deferred liability will be presented fairly in the financial statements;
The Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant conduct reconciliation of records to establish a realistic balance of receivables for the RPT Taxes and SET Taxes so that necessary adjustment(s) in the books of accounts can be effected for a more realistic presentation of the balances in the financial statements;
The Municipal Treasurer religiously update the individual Real Property Tax Account Register (RPTAR) or Taxpayer’s Index Card every time a payment is received from the taxpayer which shall serve as the basis in the preparation of the List of Delinquent Real Property Taxpayers as of the end of the year, the total of which shall equal the RPT/SET Receivable at year end;
The Local Chief Executive (LCE), Municipal Treasurer and other concerned Municipal Officials exert concerted efforts to intensify collections of long outstanding RPT and SET Receivables including the interest thereon so that more development programs may be implemented for the benefit of the constituents; and
The Municipal Accountant maintain subsidiary ledgers for RPT and SET Receivables to facilitate smooth reconciliation of balances.

We recommended that the OIC, Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Municipal Treasurer:
Exercise prudence and due diligence in the processing of transactions;
Require the accountable officers to liquidate their cash advances within the prescribed period;
Ensure that no cash advances are granted unless the previous ones are liquidated;
Ensure completeness of documents and payroll bear complete signatures of payees and proper approval before disbursements/liquidations are made;
Monitor the liquidation of cash advances by sending demand letters regularly and withhold the payment of any money due them in case of their failure to settle the liquidation of cash advances despite demand;
Conduct thorough review and evaluation of the affected dormant accounts and comply with all the documentary requirements and procedures under COA Circular 2016-005 for the proper disposition such as request for write-off and the disclosure of dormant accounts; and
See to it that all applicable laws, rules and regulations affecting cash advances and disbursement of funds are strictly adhered to.

